div1.p: Territory of Washington County of Spokane}ss.
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, Spo- kane County, in said Territory

To the Sheriff of Spokane County, Greeting: In the name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon W. R. Barthalomew and John Crane to be and appear before the at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the forthwith day of A.D. 188, at o'clock M. to there give evi- dence in the above entitled cause on the part of said plaintiff

WITNESS the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed, this 29 day of April A.D. 1885. Kate W. Feuerbach Clerk. By R. Strobach Deputy.
Territory of Washington, County of Spokane }ss.

I hereby certify that I served the within subpoena on the within named witness by reading the same to John Crane in said county, on this 29 day of April A.D. 1885 E.F. Whittier Sheriff By H.B. Mason Deputy

I do hereby certify that I used due Diligence to find Bartholomew & could not find him in said county & that I left a note of the Subpoena with his wife at this Residence in Spokan County W.T. this 29th day of April 1885 E.F. Whittier Sheriff By H.B. Mason Deputy
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, Spo- kane County, in said Territory.
Returned and filed this 2 day of May A.D. 1885 Kate W. Feuerbach Clerk By R. Strobach Deputy
SHERIFF'S FEES. Serving 1 names at 40 .40 Mileage 27 miles at 10 2.70 Total, ----$3.10
